    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>You ask rhetorically, ''Why should India and China make major sacrifices while the United States, in effect, gets a free ride?''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>You ask rhetorically, ''Why should India and China make major sacrifices while the United States, in effect, gets a free ride?''</p>
        <p>But turn that question around: ''Why should the United States make major sacrifices while China and India get a free ride?'' That provides an equally adequate justification for the United States not to ratify the Kyoto Protocol.</p>
        <p>Andrew Brett  Princeton, N.J., Dec. 13, 2005</p>
      </block>
